results.name: Huats Kee Fish Head Steamboat
results.address: 200 Turf Club Road, #01-05 The Grandstand, Singapore 287994

featured_reviews.review_text: Happy with our meal here since we dined a bit late there weren't a lot of restaurants open anymore. The fish curry was great and the chicken wings were a pleasant addition. Had to order another cup of rice - it's that good!
Great addition to Turf City. If you like Fish Head Steamboat old school style (charcoal), this is a good place to come. Soup is good, fish tastes fresh. We tried Pang Pang Chicken too, nice too!

Come for lunch, the Fish Head steamboat is really good 👍

Ordered some Zhi Char dishes as well, all good, but forgotten to snap them.

Excellent char Kueh teow, yuan Yang horfun, onion egg.

The money vegetable in egg sauce was all chopped up and a little salty. Fried rice was passable.

Next time we'll come for the charcoal fire steamboat that we see others ordering.

Delicious tangy tomato sauce horfun! Horfun is full of wokhei and the pork cutlet is thick and soft.

We had to wait for quite a while for our food so take note.

Rarely picky when eating at tzechar eateries because after all its locally run by our fellow Singaporeans. But this is definitely one of the worst experience I’ve had. Waitress was so rude. My mother asked for a certain dish and instead of replying verbally, the rude waitress simply gestured with her palm (a nonchalant wave as if waving goodbye lol) with her mouth chewing something or what?? Secondly, the moment we ordered our 4th dish, she proceeded to keep ALL our menus WHILST my parents were still looking. I asked her why the rush? She told me “oh usually 3 paxes don’t order beyond 4 dishes” hello? That’s according to your subjective experiences so far, do not generalize? Thirdly, I asked for 4 bowls of rice and she totally (acted or not idk) gave me a stunned look and then proceeds to reply me in a condescending tone. Cmon I was wearing a sports jersey, I’m tanned, I clearly do sports can’t you see? Was it necessary to react that way? Even if she can’t tell, it definitely was not POLITE to question customers unnecessarily. Seriously smh at the horrible service. Lastly, while eating she even came by our table and asked hypocritically if we needed to order more? Obviously no, because the food was nothing to rave about🤭 Nothing but lackluster. Nobody is expecting a 5 star service here, but instead the least one can provide is basic courtesy and mutual respect. Side note: the other staffs here are OK, delivering what they should and nothing more. So there’s none to pick on.

One of the worst “Tze Char” place have been to.

Spring onion ginger pork doesn’t have enough taste and sauce is watery.

Beehoon is tasteless as well.

Vegetable was acceptable.

Not worth coming.
Good Zhi char esp tomato noodles and steam fish. However they are closing down.

detailed_reviews.review_text: Having stemwd snapper fish head with black bean source. Fish head not as fresh as I expected.
Good Zhi char esp tomato noodles and steam fish. However they are closing down.
Very economical. Fish steamboat with about 11 pieces of thick thick    for a small portion (fish meat pot). Thats $48. Satisfying Food
Nothing special only their service attitude is bad especially the lady with glass and long hair. Will not recommend.
Bill $100 for 5 adults, reasonae. Fish soup is tasty and my parents keep refilling their bowls. We also ordered egg spinach, furong omelette & prawn paste chicken. All dishes were great.
Very hot.

My go to place to get home cooked food. You must try the Fish head curry which is sold out pretty fast , also order the 3 eggs spinach , just like Mums cooking. Better hurry down to the place before Grandstand is handed back to owner for re-development.
Decently priced zichar, friendly staff. Must try the prawn roll!

Fish steamboat was nice and tasty. waitress was friendly. They provided  us with good recommendations so that we can have more variety of dishes. Down side was there were not enough seats. so to grab a seat, you better come early.

Came on Friday at around 6pm plus, told the nice aunt that I dont have any reservation,  and she immediately help me to reserve a table of 8 pax. I told her my family members will reach another 7min. Tasty foods, have the nostalgia taste. The prawns chicken paste doesnt taste salty.  The fish steamboat wow... so tasty, dont have the after taste thirst. Vegetables nice too.  We ordered six dishes.The beautiful lady. Thank you for your services.

Went on Saturday night for dinner. Ordered the fish meat steamboat, prawn paste chicken, and marmite chicken rice set. The soup was amazing, v savoury and the other dishes met my expectations too. Dont know why people review the food for bad taste. Tasted great to me. Didn t take photos tho. Only downside is the ridiculously long wait time. I think I waited 40min + for my food   got my starving. But recommend to go if you got some time and around the area.

Was there on a Tuesday afternoon after the usual lunch hour. Hence ample table spaces and ordering was easy. Verbally told waitress of order, food came, after eating we ate paid at the counter. The noodle and rice dishes are approx $6 to $8. The zichar dishes are from $10. The steamboat fishhead starts from $28. Very decent place for aircon, free parking and flavourful food in Bukit Timah. The shops in Turf City are moving out by the end of 2023 as SLA did not renew the master tenants lease after its expiry in end 2023.

Bad experience! Rude and unfriendly staff and service! We queued and asked if can make reservations, and was told cant as already full and asked to look for own tables. We waited for about 20-25mins and saw patrons of a table leaving and went over to the table and wanted to sit down as they stood up. A staff came over and said the table was for customers seated at next smaller table who had 5 pax. I was unhappy and told that your staff told us to look for own table. Now I found one, and was told they reserved for customers seated at next table who had 5 pax. And well, we had 5 of us too!! And they kept arguing that that group came first and 5 pax cant fit that table they were at, and asked 5 of us to sit on that smaller table! If that table cant fit that group with 5 pax, then why can it fit 5 of us then?? And please, do not ask customers to look for own table then since youve pre-arranged seating for your other customers!!
Usually the cashier would pass you the buzzer and receipt, never have i seen a cashier throw (literally) the buzzer and receipt on the tray rudely.
Come for lunch, the Fish Head steamboat is really good Ordered some Zhi Char dishes as well, all good, but forgotten to snap them. Food : 5/5
Decently nice fish head steamboat at Grandstand. Fish is fresh and zi char is nice
Nice cosy plc for dinner. Prices varies. Seating limited.

Happy with our meal here since we dined a bit late there werent a lot of restaurants open anymore. The fish curry was great and the chicken wings were a pleasant addition. Had to order another cup of rice - its that good!
Will still visit again only when there is not much customers there, services can improve.
Long queue.. Wait long
Food is good and cheap!

The fish was sooo fresh!! That i even saw the fish gave birth and swam to the other table that came after us! Waited >50mins yet nth was served bcoz of a mixed up. They did not have the courtesy to inform us and apologize until we had to ask.  Whats best was that they recommended us the dishes and i would recommend not to ever come here!!

Terrible service , we ordered 1 fish head steamboat , 1 tofu and 1 veg . Waited for 50mins and nothing is served. The table after us gotten their fish head ahead of us. When i approach the chef , they say they took the wrong fish , yet none of our other dishes were prepared. They should have at least inform us of the wrong fish and we would have taken it. It wasnt even busy , there was only 4 table. If you cant even manage 4 table , you should just close down.

Food is not bad but service is seriously bad. They are quite rude and impatient and they dont even clear/clean the tables thoroughly, all halfway done. I had to wipe the table myself. Waited for more than 50 mins for the first dish to be served. The table that came after alrdy got their food. Do not recommend coming if you are hungry, might faint.
Not nice. Waiting time long.
Lousy restaurant. Food serving is very slow. One of the older aunty waitress is very very rude. Will not come back again. Also wun advise other to come.

Lousy service, came in when no around. Ordered a steam song fish head with black bean sauce and a soup. After that 2 guy came in to order 2 rice set, follow by a lady ordered 5 rice set. The cook, cook the 2 packet then the 5 packet for take away. After that took 5mins to cook our soup follow by another 10 min for our fish to come. Total waited for almost 35mins for us to get our food.  I thought it should be first come first serve. Will not come again, the food is not that excellent  to wait that long. Service sucks especially  for the cook.
Tasty fish soup and a range of reasonably priced tze char dishes in a rustic and homey setting. Service was fine too.
Waited for an hour only to be told when we complained that they lost our order. And that was that. They did nothing. Horrendous experience. Highly regret suggesting this to my parents.
Decided to try after passing by so many times . Not bad with reasonable price  they are under the   group..
Service was a little disappointing, the cereal prawns were kinda bland but salted egg chickens were not bad.
The best threadfin fish steam boat with delectable dishes to pair with

Located at Turf City, and thing abt Turf City is that there s always free parking - so definitely a plus Food was good. Had the fish head steamboat which was nice. Not sure what market norm is but we had free top up of soup too, so that was great. Wait for the food was however a bit long - took 25 minutes for the first dish to arrive. Also, the place is a bit loud - very echoy although I m not sure if fault lies more with Turf City s build or specifically with Huats Kee s.
Delicious tangy tomato sauce horfun! Horfun is full of wokhei and the pork cutlet is thick and soft. We had to wait for quite a while for our food so take note.

Service was very slow on a Sunday night despite some empty tables. Waited more than 45 mins for our large fish head steamboat + 2 side dishes. Only received food after many reminders to the staff. Food was below average - fish soup had little flavour. Side dishes such as oyster omelette were forgettable.

We had the homemade tofu claypot $12. V gd w broccolli, la la, fish slices. Ipoh fried pork - $10 or $12. It was a gd portion of pork covered w har cheong paste. Taste was gd because har cheong not too overpowering. Hae cho had water chestnut but a bit meaty smelling for us. Food in 10mins. Coke in cans $1. Aircon zhi char at decent value for a quick lunch.
Slow serving time. Fish soup smell too fishy, shouldnt be like that.
Service is slow, waited for 30mins for few simple dishes when there are still free tables. Food tasted just meh..
enjoyed the charcoal fish steamboat, soup was flavourful and the chilli sauce that comes with the dishes really packed a punch and matched the fish perfectly!
Service
Service is fast but no due diligence.

Order large    fish head steamboat,  s$38. But only half fishhead, wonder if order small Only one quarter fish head ? Overall taste 50/50 just normal. But compare to the price is abnormal,  service is fast but quantity of the food is small. Will not visit again and will not recommend to my dear friends.
If you love to deal with an arrogant head waiter, this place is for you.  Otherwise, please support the other outlets.
Terrible service.

Absolutely horrendous experience waiting more than one hour for food to be served. Those coming with old folks and children please AVOID AT ALL COSTS. They have a system of serving table by table. So if the table before you is full table with lots of order, good luck to you. Food so so.
Wait very long with little customer, rude service. Food normal.
One of the worst  Tze Char  place have been to. Spring onion ginger pork doesn t have enough taste and sauce is watery. Beehoon is tasteless as well. Vegetable was acceptable. Not worth coming.
Food was average and the wait felt long even though we had dinner at about 5 plus pm.

Overall, the food was good; not impressive but no complains considering that we polished off the dishes. However, the service is extremely disappointing; particularly from a lady staff who gives a nonchalant attitude and look (yes, even with the mask on you could get that from her). It felt so uncomfortable that dining at the premise was an experience that we had to be wary of the staffs mood. Being rude, does not have to be verbalised - this was the case. I have to say, this will be our first and last visit to the restaurant.
Reasonably priced zhi char restaurant in air-conditioned mall. The fish hotpot is delicious.

The osyter omelette is so salty it taste just right out of the sea. The butter pork so is tough and taste bland. Sambal kang kong was so so, the only edible food. Came at about 2.45pm, only one table and the staff kept forgetting the orders.

We have been to this place many times, they are considered one of the top place for fish head steamboat. Fresh fish and the full rich flavors of the amazing broth are the reason we keep coming back. Best to come on weekdays if you want to beat the lines.

Extemely long waiting time. Not organise at all. Have no idea how to operate an FnB operation at all. Cant believe at the 1 hour mark, 3rd dish wasnt delivered. Only inform us that they wont be able to deliver the dish when we start asking why the dish was not ready? My house coffeeshop can provide a better service skills and quality food. Not recommended. Not coming back anymore.
Tasty and affordable Zi Char

Service was really, really slow, waited 45mins just for the first dish to come, followed by another 10mins just for utensils. And then it took another 15mins each for the subsequent dishes to arrive. The staff did explain that it was their busy period. Dishes ordered came in smaller-than-expected serving portions. Overall taste-wise was delicious though. Would recommend to come during off peak or make reservations.

Parking here is free and easy. I am not surprised that this restaurant is always packed with long queue in the weekends,  the efficient staff and the quality of the food are certainly up to standard. Their aromatic broth is super addictive and they use charcoal to keep it warm for a long time! Unpretentious and delicious, this is a restaurant you will never want to miss !
Fish head steamboat is good
The fish head steamnoat soup is delious, with big chunks of fish meat

Excellent char Kueh teow, yuan Yang horfun, onion egg. The money vegetable in egg sauce was all chopped up and a little salty. Fried rice was passable. Next time well come for the charcoal fire steamboat that we see others ordering.
Great addition to Turf City. If you like Fish Head Steamboat old school style (charcoal), this is a good place to come. Soup is good, fish tastes fresh. We tried Pang Pang Chicken too, nice too!

Seriously if you want a good meal, don t try here. The butter pork has the burnt taste and inedible. Even the ice Horlick drink is sweeten to the core and you need another glass of water and ice to dilute. The water chestnut drink has a weird taste and I returned it immediately The oyster egg...oh my is full of salt
Stumbled upon this place and ordered a couple of tze char dishes. The Straits Times has reviewed their fishhead steamboat to be of excellent quality. Their homemade beancurd dish is also delicious!
